    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including the installation of a dual-row ceramic IMS bearing and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). The chassis remains composed on Bilstein B6 dampers, while the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback lost in later generations. Braking performance is sharp, utilizing four-piston monobloc calipers and ventilated rotors. While the exterior shows light patina from spirited use, the mechanical vitals are robust and the cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temp thermostat.",
