      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Up for sale is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. This chassis has been properly sorted with a reinforced rear subframe and a comprehensive VANOS system overhaul to ensure timing precision and long-term reliability. Power is delivered through a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox to the rear wheels via the factory M Variable Differential Lock. The suspension geometry is maintained by refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers, preserving the car's legendary 50/50 weight distribution. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical vitals are excellent, with recent Blackstone oil reports confirming healthy rod bearing wear. A mechanically sound, analog performance icon ready for the twisties.",
